@node "intro" "Introduction to the Championship"

            The Amateur Internet Formula One World Championship

                           Short Introduction



 The Amatuer Formula One World Championship is aimed at those of you
 out there who have succesfully mastered how to win at Microprose's
 F1 Grand Prix and are now looking for a more competitive enviroment
 to race in after all you dont have to play the game for too long
 before beating the computer controlled cars becomes pretty easy.

 So when this happens you've got a few options until now you've had
 practice until you've been good enough to race at semi-pro level
 then you could join the Internet Formula One Championship, Which is
 an excellently run championship , If your good enough to drive at
 semi-pro or Ace you should check out there web site at
 http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/AmigaF1.html

 If how ever your not good enough to race at either of those levels
 The Amateur Internet Formula One World Championship ( AIC from now on)
 is probably what your looking for.
 Best of all its totally free and should hopefully by the end of the
 16 race season helped you improve your skills.

 If you have any Comments , Questions or queries feel free to ask 
 send email to              aic@f1world.demon.co.uk


