@node "join" "How to Join the AIC"

        The Amatuer Internet Formula One World Championship

                        How to Join



 There are FIVE steps to joining the AIC

 Step ONE

 You should get the latest copy of Oliver Roberts F1GP-ED from Aminet
 it is in the directory game/misc (F1GP-ED is SHAREWARE please support
 it and keep great utilitys such as F1GP-Ed being made)

 Once you have F1gp-ed installed load your f1gp binary file into f1gp-ed
 and change the following settings

 TEAMS

  Set this to 13  and highlight the Normal Risk Factor box.
  You can use whichever team number you want , make sure you
  change the team name and add your name as the driver and
  select the none option as your teamate.
  Horsepower must be set to 716.
  Change your car colour and pit crew if you want.


 Drivers

 Delete one of the drivers names and add your own ,
 Change your helmet design if you want.

 Car Control

 Select whichever control method you want to use.

 Standard Options

 Select Auto Gears - Dotted Best Line and Suggested Gear.
 Practice session time can be whatever you want
 Qualifying must be 30 minutes
 Race Distance should be set to 40%
 
 Preferences

 Set wet race proability to 0% if there is to be a wet race
 in the season you can change this to 100% before the race
 and resave your f1gp binary file.
  
 Cheats

 Unselect everything in this window
 and make sure player Hp is 716 and Finish Hp is also 716.

 Display

 Frames/Sec: should be changed to 10


 And thats you now got a Amateur Internet F1GP Champioship version
 of Formula One Grand Prix. Thats also the hardest part of joining
 the Championship over with aswell.

 Step TWO
 
 Now you have to send an email with the following Information in it...

 Name :(must be your full name)
 Email Address:(an address where results etc can be sent)
 Team Name:(obvious)
 Questions etc:

 send this email to aic@f1world.demon.co.uk

 Step THREE

 You will be sent a comfirmation and a copy of the rules (incase they've
 been revised)

 Step FOUR

 Wait for an email which will contain the Race Season Calendar.

 Step FIVE

 Get racing :)


